  "text": "Note that the argument in [CITATION_1] uses a combinaison of algebraic properties coming from integrability theory (linearized Miura transformation) and of refined PDE tools. The use of exponentially weighted spaces in this context is also related to [CITATION_2] . Interestingly, it is necessary to consider parameters σ and c depending on t and y. We refer to [CITATION_3] for more precise statements. Note that the scaling parameter c(t, y) converges to 1; indeed, a localized perturbation cannot provoke a change in the scaling of the infinite energy line-soliton. Another recent result [CITATION_4] weakens the assumption on the initial data.",
